* saving and loading graph efficiently

* output: show recursion depth when printing e.g. the dependencies
  -> one space shows recursion depth 1, two spaces = depth 2, ...

* cleanup function naming

* new feature: fuzzy matching
  -> so that the user can e.g. type packages without version numbers like 'dependencies -u nano'

* do a test run with data of whole system
  -> therefore use ldd, readelf, ... to fetch the information
  -> get all packages with `BEE_METADIR=/usr/share/bee bee list`
  -> data can be found at /usr/share/bee/<pkg-name>/FILES

* always check memory leaks:
  valgrind -v --show-reachable=yes --smc-check=all --leak-check=full ./dependencies
